<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54145c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54145c">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54145c"> 145(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> twin doll</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Comme beaucoup d&apos;autres Africains, les Cabrais sont persuad&eacute;s que <mark>les jumeaux</mark> n&apos;ont pour eux deux qu&apos;un seul principe vital, qui ne se divise pas. Si l&apos;un vient &agrave; mourir, l&apos;autre ne pourra pis rester vivant. Pour qu&apos;il &eacute;chappe &agrave; la mort, il faut donc faire en sorte que son fr&egrave;re, quoique d&eacute;funt, continue &agrave; coexister avec lui. A cette fin, <mark>on en fabrique un double, un substitut</mark>. <br><font color="green">[Like many other Africans, the Cabrats are convinced that the twins have only one vital principle for them, which does not divide. If one dies, the other cannot stay alive. In order for him to escape death, it is therefore necessary to ensure that his brother, although deceased, continues to coexist with him. To this end, we make a double, a substitute.]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 222</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
